fix: predictedduplicates containing empty strings (#218)

Removed samples (from QC) would have "" in their spot in
predictedduplicates. These are then clustered together in the table call
below, resulting in section 4.2 giving a confusing result (saying these
samples belong to the same individual despite being removed). This no
longer occurs

Use full file paths instead of globs in s/f tests (#153)

* Use full file paths instead of globs in tests

Previously there was a chance that certain samples had multiple matches
for the glob patterns in the extended tests. For example, a sample might
    have both broad and narrow peaks. In such scenarios, the tests would
    break due to there being too many positional arguments.

Add advice to guide on using the `--rebase` flag when pulling (#143)

* Add advice on using the --rebase flag when pulling

* remove misleading word

This line is intended to tell the user what to do after/if the `git pull --rebase` command fails. Not what to do instead of using `git pull --rebase`. I think the distinction is important as if you are only doing `git pull` from the start, then the `git rebase --abort` command isn't doing anything and git complain with:
```
fatal: No rebase in progress?
```
